=== Sprint 2 · Task S2.4: ConnectAccount → real MT connect via NATS ===
Date: 2026-05-27
Plan: docs/plan/2026-05-27-整改与执行计划.md §4.S2.4

--- Problem ---
V2 §2.D-3 / plan S2.4: ConnectAccount handler only updated PG status. There was no
mechanism to notify the mdgateway runner to actually connect/disconnect accounts.
The full lifecycle was: user clicks Connect → PG status changes → nothing else happens.
mdgateway only loaded accounts at startup and never picked up new connections.

--- Fix ---
Part 1 — internal/mdgateway/account_events.go (NEW):
- AccountEventPublisher: publishes account lifecycle events to NATS JetStream
- Subjects: account.connect, account.disconnect, account.reconnect
- AccountEvent JSON schema: {account_id, user_id, timestamp}
- Nil-safe: if js is nil, events are silently dropped (for testing)

Part 2 — internal/connect/user/account_handler.go (MODIFIED):
- Added publisher *mdgateway.AccountEventPublisher field + SetPublisher() setter
- ConnectAccount: after PG status update, publishes account.connect event
- DisconnectAccount: after PG status update, publishes account.disconnect event
- ReconnectAccount: after PG status update, publishes account.reconnect event
- All three: publisher nil-safe (skips publish when not configured)

Part 3 — internal/mdgateway/runner.go (MODIFIED):
- Added startAccountEventSubscriber(ctx, nc, log) function
- Subscribes to "account.>" wildcard, logs received account lifecycle events
- Full dynamic gateway reload deferred to phase 2 (S2.4-m2)
- Called from Run() after health monitor, before <-ctx.Done()

Part 4 — internal/mdgateway/wiring.go (MODIFIED):
- Added loadSingleAccountConfig(ctx, pg, accountID) for future dynamic reload
- Queries mt_accounts_v2 WHERE id = $1 AND is_active = true

Part 5 — cmd/server/main.go (MODIFIED):
- Created AccountEventPublisher(js, log) after NATS JetStream init
- Injected into accountServer via SetPublisher()

